  "An international treaty to protect a globally important ecosystem is signed by 180 countries. However, five years later, monitoring reveals that the ecosystem continues to decline because many signatory nations have not implemented the required policies. A major industrialized nation argues it should not have to comply because its competitors are not complying either. What two challenges of international environmental governance does this scenario illustrate?": "",
