  "A new synthetic chemical is being proposed for widespread agricultural use. Laboratory studies show it may persist in the environment for decades and could accumulate in food chains, but research is still incomplete. Environmental groups demand it be banned until proven safe, while the chemical company says there is no conclusive evidence of harm. Which principle would support the environmental groups' position?": "",
  "The polluter pays principle": "",
  "The principle of Prior Informed Consent": "",
  "The principle of national sovereignty": "",
  "The precautionary principle supports taking preventive action against potential environmental harm even when scientific certainty is not yet complete, placing the burden of proof on those proposing potentially harmful activities.": "",
  "A small island nation that contributes less than 0.01% of global greenhouse gas emissions is facing sea level rise that threatens its very existence. It proposes that major emitting nations should provide financial assistance for adaptation. This situation highlights which aspect of international environmental policy?": "",
