  "The free-rider problem in fisheries management": "",
  "The principle of common but differentiated responsibilities and climate equity": "",
  "This scenario illustrates the principle of common but differentiated responsibilities, which recognizes that while all nations share environmental challenges, historically large emitters bear greater responsibility for addressing climate impacts on vulnerable nations.": "",
  "Scientists discover that a widely used refrigerant is damaging the ozone layer, but the refrigeration industry argues that alternatives are too expensive. Developing nations say they cannot afford to switch. After negotiations, developed nations agree to fund the transition in developing countries, and affordable alternatives are developed. This scenario mirrors which historical treaty?": "",
